---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Bane Sullivan"
  description="Senior engineer, geophysicist, and open-source developer building tools that make 3D and geospatial visualization intuitive and powerful."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="hero">
    <img src="/profile.jpeg" alt="Bane Sullivan" width="96" height="96" />
    <div class="hero-text">
      <h1>Bane Sullivan</h1>
      <p class="tagline">Senior Engineer &middot; Geophysicist &middot; Open-Source Developer</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Links -->
  <nav class="nav-links">
    <a href="https://github.com/banesullivan">GitHub</a>
    <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bane-sullivan">LinkedIn</a>
    <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=jslLe0cAAAAJ">Google Scholar</a>
    <a href="https://blog.banesullivan.com">Blog</a>
    <a href="mailto:banesullivan@gmail.com">Email</a>
  </nav>

  <!-- About -->
  <section class="section intro">
    <p>
      I build tools and platforms that make complex spatial data intuitive and
      accessible. My open-source work is used by thousands of researchers and engineers
      worldwide, with projects reaching 500k+ monthly downloads and adoption across
      2,000+ codebases.
    </p>
    <p>
      My background is in applied earth sciences (B.Sc. Geophysics, M.Sc. Hydrology, both from
      Colorado School of Mines). That foundation led me to the intersection of 3D visualization,
      geospatial data, and reproducible workflows, which eventually led me to building software
      platforms full-time. I've shipped products at research-driven startups and enterprise R&D
      organizations, from early prototypes to production systems used across entire companies.
    </p>
    <p>
      I genuinely believe that scientific findings should be reproducible, not only by other
      researchers but also by the stakeholders of the science at hand. I carry this sentiment in
      everything I build.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- Experience -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2>Experience</h2>

    <div class="experience-item">
      <h3>KoBold Metals <span class="role">Senior Software Engineer</span></h3>
      <div class="dates">2023 &ndash; 2025</div>
      <p>
        Developed and deployed a collaborative analysis and 3D visualization platform
        bridging geologists and data scientists. Pushed adoption of cloud-native geospatial
        standards (STAC) and streamlined access to computational tools across the organization.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-item">
      <h3>Kitware, Inc. <span class="role">Senior R&D Engineer</span></h3>
      <div class="dates">2020 &ndash; 2023</div>
      <p>
        Lead developer for Pan3D (3D visualization for PanGeo) and ResonantGeoData
        (geospatial data management). Built enterprise-scale systems and helped
        procure $1.8M+ in commercial contracts and government grants.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="experience-item">
      <h3>Colorado School of Mines <span class="role">Graduate Researcher</span></h3>
      <div class="dates">2018 &ndash; 2020</div>
      <p>
        Explored the intersection of 3D visualization, geoscience, and reproducible workflows.
        Created PyVista and other open-source tools to make 3D scientific computing accessible.
        Awarded the Mendenhall Prize for outstanding M.Sc. student in Geophysics.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- Projects -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2>Open Source</h2>

    <div class="project-item">
      <h3><a href="https://docs.pyvista.org">PyVista</a></h3>
      <p class="project-meta">Creator & lead maintainer &middot; NumFOCUS affiliated &middot; 500k+ monthly downloads</p>
      <p>
        3D visualization and mesh analysis through a streamlined interface for VTK.
        Used by 2,000+ open-source projects and 600+ downstream packages across
        engineering, geophysics, and scientific computing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-item">
      <h3><a href="https://github.com/banesullivan/localtileserver">localtileserver</a></h3>
      <p class="project-meta">Creator &middot; 50k+ monthly downloads &middot; used in 600+ projects</p>
      <p>
        Dynamic tile serving for interactive visualization of large geospatial rasters
        directly in Jupyter notebooks.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="project-item">
      <h3><a href="https://github.com/ResonantGeoData">ResonantGeoData</a></h3>
      <p class="project-meta">Lead developer at Kitware</p>
      <p>
        Geospatial data management and search API built on Django, designed for cataloging
        and serving large imagery assets in machine learning pipelines.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- Education -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2>Education</h2>

    <div class="education-item">
      <h3>M.Sc. Hydrology</h3>
      <p class="details">Colorado School of Mines &middot; 2018&ndash;2020 &middot; Hydrological Science & Engineering</p>
    </div>

    <div class="education-item">
      <h3>B.Sc. Geophysics</h3>
      <p class="details">Colorado School of Mines &middot; 2014&ndash;2018 &middot; Minor in Computer Science</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- Closing -->
  <section class="section intro">
    <p>
      Beyond all the coding and science, I'm a trail runner, mountain biker, and general
      human-powered adventure enthusiast. Feel free to
      <a href="mailto:banesullivan@gmail.com">reach out</a>, I'm always happy to talk about
      earth science computing, open-source software, or epic outdoor activities.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
